===================================== GOAL =====================================

  Automatized the analysis of an application


===================================== USAGE ====================================

usage: analysis.py [-h] [--emulator EMULATOR] [--phone PHONE] [--proxy PROXY]
                   [--proxy_cert PROXY_CERT]
                   app

Analysis for smartphone

positional arguments:
  app                   app target <filename.apk>

optional arguments:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit

dynamic:
  --emulator EMULATOR   path of the emulator if used
  --phone PHONE         phones target emulator -list-avds
  --proxy PROXY         setup proxy address <ip>:<port>
  --proxy_cert PROXY_CERT
                        setup proxy address <filename>.cer
  --files_store         store all files read or written by application


=================================== EXEMPLE ====================================

python3 src/analysis.py <example>.apk --emulator ~/Android/Sdk/tools/ \
        --phone Pixel_3a_XL_API_22 --proxy 127.0.0.1:8080 --proxy_cert burp.der

# To list all emulator phone avaible
emulator -list-avds

================================= REQUIREMENT ==================================

This project needed to use the sdktools the path is specify with the option
--sdktools <path>

To install sdktools and the less extrathings you should download
commandlinetools: https://developer.android.com/studio/index.html#command-tools

```bash
$ wget https://dl.google.com/android/repository/commandlinetools-linux-6200805_latest.zip
$ mkdir <sdktoolspath>
$ cd <sdktoolspath>
$ unzip commandlinetools-linux-6200805_latest.zip
```

To list all package available:
```bash
$ tools/bin/sdkmanager --list --sdk_root=.
```

Install the minimum with the correct version when I written that it's look like
that:

```bash
tools/bin/sdkmanager "platforms;android-R" "build-tools;30.0.0-rc4" "emulator" --sdk_root=.
```

To use jadx decompiler:
```
cd src/submodule/jadx
./gradlew dist
```



